main event: Multiple witnesses in Scarsdale, New York observed two objects shaped like cones joined at the base flying at an estimated altitude of 10,000 feet on July 31, 1963.
interesting points: Witnesses described the objects as having flight characteristics similar to large airplanes., The sighting lasted a few minutes and included detailed witness descriptions., Forms were submitted for further investigation, indicating possible aircraft behavior., There were conflicting reports about the nature of the objects, with some suggesting that they were not aircraft., The report notes that no photographs were included with the sighting documentation.
sighted object: Two cone-shaped objects joined at the base
witness description: Witnesses included both male and female residents of Scarsdale, with varying ages.
